messageBody:
James Keirstead wrote:
> Thanks to everyone for their advice on this. I haven't figured out
> exactly what's going on yet but from what you've said, I've tracked it
> down to the following.
>
> The problem appears to be with a HashMap. It works fine when there is
> only one key/value pair to be added but it breaks when more than one
> item are added. The following code fragement demonstrates the issue.

One question with maps:

What type are the /keys/ in your HashMap? Are they are custom class of
yours? If so, is the hash code consistent with Equals()?
